@page "/about"

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>About This App</h1>
    <p>A real-world Blazor WebAssembly showcase built with enterprise C# patterns.</p>
</div>

<div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-card">
        <h3>⚡ WebAssembly</h3>
        <p>
            Blazor WASM compiles C# to WebAssembly bytecode. The .NET runtime runs
            directly in your browser — no Node.js, no transpilation, no JS framework.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-card">
        <h3>🔐 AuthSaas SDK</h3>
        <p>
            Authentication is handled by the <strong>AuthSaas.Client</strong> NuGet package —
            the same C# SDK available for any .NET project. JWT tokens are stored in sessionStorage
            via JS interop.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-card">
        <h3>🏗️ Clean Architecture</h3>
        <p>
            Services are injected via .NET's built-in DI container. Interfaces decouple
            the domain from infrastructure — the same patterns used in production .NET backends.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-card">
        <h3>🐘 PHP + MySQL Backend</h3>
        <p>
            Data is persisted in MySQL on Apache shared hosting via a PHP REST API.
            Requests are authenticated with Bearer tokens verified by the PHP JWT library.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card" style="margin-top:1rem">
    <h3 style="font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:0.75rem">Tech Stack</h3>
    <div class="tech-list">
        <span class="tech-pill">Blazor WASM</span>
        <span class="tech-pill">C# 13</span>
        <span class="tech-pill">.NET 9</span>
        <span class="tech-pill">AuthSaas.Client</span>
        <span class="tech-pill">PHP 8</span>
        <span class="tech-pill">MySQL</span>
        <span class="tech-pill">PDO</span>
        <span class="tech-pill">Apache</span>
    </div>
</div>
